b'[Sacred Texts](../../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../../index.htm)\n[Tagore](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)  [Previous](cm36.htm)\n[Next](cm38.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n### THE BANYAN TREE\n\nO you shaggy-headed banyan tree standing on the bank of the pond, have you\nforgotten the little child, like the birds that have nested in your branches\nand left you?\n\nDo you not remember how he sat at the window and wondered at the tangle of\nyour roots that plunged underground?\n\nThe women would come to fill their jars in the pond, and your huge black\nshadow would wriggle on the water like sleep struggling to wake up.\n\nSunlight danced on the ripples like restless tiny shuttles weaving golden\ntapestry.\n\nTwo ducks swam by the weedy margin above their shadows, and the child would\nsit still and think.\n\nHe longed to be the wind and blow through your rustling branches, to be your\nshadow and lengthen with the day on the water, to be a bird and perch on your\ntop-most twig, and to float like those ducks among the weeds and shadows.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: Benediction](cm38.htm)\n\n'